## Step 2 — Download one sample task locally

Run this once to pull a single task to your machine:

```python
# save as: download_sample.py
from huggingface_hub import hf_hub_download
from pathlib import Path
import tarfile

TASK_ID = "arvo:1065"   # jq project — small, clean C codebase, good for testing

out_dir = Path("data/arvo/1065")
out_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

print("Downloading tarball...")
tarball = hf_hub_download(
    repo_id="sunblaze-ucb/cybergym",
    filename="data/arvo/1065/repo-vul.tar.gz",
    repo_type="dataset",
    local_dir=str(out_dir),
)

print("Downloading description...")
desc = hf_hub_download(
    repo_id="sunblaze-ucb/cybergym",
    filename="data/arvo/1065/description.txt",
    repo_type="dataset",
    local_dir=str(out_dir),
)

print(f"Done. Files in {out_dir}:")
for f in out_dir.rglob("*"):
    print(f"  {f}")
```

```bash
python download_sample.py
```

