## Step 3 — Start vLLM serving Gemma

In a **separate terminal**, start your vLLM server. Pick whichever Gemma fits your GPU:

```bash
# If you have ~24GB VRAM (Gemma 27B):
python -m vllm.entrypoints.openai.api_server \
    --model google/gemma-3-27b-it \
    --port 8000 \
    --max-model-len 8192

# If you have ~12GB VRAM (Gemma 12B):
python -m vllm.entrypoints.openai.api_server \
    --model google/gemma-3-12b-it \
    --port 8000 \
    --max-model-len 8192

# If you have ~8GB VRAM (Gemma 4B):
python -m vllm.entrypoints.openai.api_server \
    --model google/gemma-3-4b-it \
    --port 8000 \
    --max-model-len 8192
```

Wait until you see `Uvicorn running on http://0.0.0.0:8000` before continuing.

**Verify it's alive in another terminal:**
```bash
curl http://localhost:8000/v1/models
```
You should see your model name in the JSON response.

---

## Step 4 — Run the CRS on your sample

```bash
python -m crs.main \
    --task-dir ./data/arvo/1065 \
    --output-dir ./crs_results \
    --model google/gemma-3-27b-it \
    --base-url http://localhost:8000/v1 \
    --api-key EMPTY \
    --no-fuzzing
```

Change `--model` to match whichever Gemma you started in Step 3.

